76561198198727003,Recommended,307190,18026466,"Posted: 13 September, 2015",all,xspdr8crx,"I actually really liked this game.  The art is pretty cute and I don't really mind that it is a points based game (like Tokimeki, you have to build stats).There were a few things that I wish were different.First I would have liked more gallery pics.  You only get 2 per guy.Second, I wish the storyline diverged sooner than it does.  The entire game spans three and a half months and I feel that you repeat the entire first month and a half for each guy.  Additionally, until the ending scene the final half month is also the same.  That said you really only get a solid three weeks or so of independent story for the guy you chose.Third, the dialogue is a little cheesy.All-in-all even with the the downsides I enjoyed the game, and since I bought it when it was 50% off the price was right.  I recommend buying it when there is a sale - it will help compensate for some of the repetitiveness :)"
