76561198120993683,Recommended,307190,17542562,"Posted: 14 August, 2015",all,bunnymistressaya,"I am a little mixed about this game but like it enough to give a positive recommendation. I give it a recommendation because I like the art and 2 characters and there is something likable in a “home grown” visual novel which targets an English speaking audience (leaning toward American as they are in Florida)The art is really made me buy this game. I think it's geared more to a English speaking audience but doesn't cross into the line of silly cartoon style of the West. Also the character designs are cute and the clothes are defiantly something that you would see an American college student wear rather than a Japanese/Korean. I think this makes the characters more likable because I felt like I was back in my own college days and these could be my own friends, where as characters targeted at a Japanese/Korean market always make me feel a little alienated, even though I did study in Japan for half a semester.The writing isn't bad, but has an overly simple plot. I'm really not huge on raising sims, I just want to read the story, so my view would probably more skewed toward the quality of the story. I felt quite a bit let down after solving the “big mystery” of the game, there is much potential for a much more in depth story. There is a bit of surprise on one path that I did enjoy, but I don't want to spoil the game in a review.However after playing so many VN/Otome games made from the Japanese market, it felt really refreshing to play a game that was actually targeting English speakers. Culture references, ways of speaking, quirks that make characters more interesting (accents, etc), characters that were designed to target English speakers all make this game more unique.  Also stereotypical characters can even be interesting when you feel like there are so many rehashed characters in the Japanese market (more seen in mobile games).The game play isn't bad, but I'm not huge on stat raising games. It took me  a bit of time to find the best way to raise the stats but after that it got a tad bit boring. I like games that at least try to add a bit of dialogue for every time a stat is raised, makes it feel a bit more exciting than just simply dry game play of stat raising games.TLDR- Buy this game if you are looking for something different than the standard otome game"
